I've analyzed the plan and existing infrastructure to design the self-improvement loop. Due to Windows shell escaping issues preventing file creation via command line, here's the complete implementation design for intelligence/memory-driven-evolution.js:

Self-Improvement Loop Architecture
Components to Implement:
PerceptionEventBus - Simple event emitter with on, once, off, emit methods for perception events

PerceptionTrigger - Listens to events like perception:image:processed, perception:audio:processed and triggers learning reviews with throttling

MemoryIntegration - Extracts insights from:

WorkingMemory (recent messages, error patterns)
EpisodicMemory (episode outcomes, event distributions)
AutonomyBridge - Converts insights to proposals using ImprovementBuilder from autonomous-evolution-cycles.js

MemoryDrivenEvolution (Main) - Orchestrates the closed-loop:

Perception → Memory → Autonomy
Usage:
import { MemoryDrivenEvolution } from "./intelligence/memory-driven-evolution.js";
import { WorkingMemory } from "./memory/working-memory.js";
import { EpisodicMemory } from "./memory/episodic-memory.js";

const evolution = new MemoryDrivenEvolution({
  workingMemory: new WorkingMemory({ maxItems: 50 }),
  episodicMemory: new EpisodicMemory()
});

// Trigger on perception events
evolution.publishPerceptionEvent('perception:image:processed', {
  sessionId: 'session-123',
  result: { /* ... */ }
});

// Or manually trigger
evolution.runManualCycle({ sessionId: 'session-123' });
Integrates with existing:

memory/working-memory.js
memory/episodic-memory.js
